record_data.record_plain_text: WATERBURY GENERATION LLC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF 1. Availability: Waterbury Generation LLC ("WatGen") makes electric energy and capacity available under this FERC electric tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. WatGen also makes available, to any purchaser, ancillary services except as prohibited below: a. PJM: WatGen offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. b. New York: WatGen offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. c. New England: WatGen offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. d. Third Party Provider: Third-party ancillary services: Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 2. Applicability: This tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity and ancillary services by WatGen at market-based rates. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and WatGen. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between WatGen and the purchaser. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: WatGen shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning WatGen's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes WatGen to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits WatGen's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning WatGen's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: WatGen has been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market-based rate authority: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 regarding the filing of rate schedules, except Sections 35.12(a), 35.12(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of the accounting and related reporting requirements under Parts 41, 101 with the exception that waiver of the provisions that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects, and 141 of the Commission's regulations except for Sections 141.14 and 141.15; and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumptions of liabilities. See Waterbury Generation, LLC, Letter Order Granting Market-Based Rate Authorization, Docket No. ER08-200-000 (December 26, 2007). 7. Effective Date: This tariff is effective upon the date authorized by the Commission. 8. Seller Category: WatGen is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Northeast Region, and a Category 1 seller in all other Regions.
